image = cv2.imread("handgreyscale.jpg")  # Load Image
image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)  
image_in_pixels = image.reshape((-1, 3))   # Reshape as 2D matrix:  W*H x 3  
image_in_pixels = np.float32(image_in_pixels)   # convert to float

#### Run KMeans using python OpenCV  
_, pixels, (centers) = cv2.kmeans(image_in_pixels, 2, None, (cv2.TERM_CRITERIA_EPS + cv2.TERM_CRITERIA_MAX_ITER, 100, 0.2), 10, cv2.KMEANS_RANDOM_CENTERS)
centers = np.uint8(centers)     # 8 bit integers
pixels = pixels.flatten()     # flatten the labels array
result_image = centers[pixels.flatten()] 
result_image = result_image.reshape(image.shape) # reshape as normal image in 3D(W X H X RGB)

Maxval = 251

win=Tk()

x1,y1,x2,y2,counter =  IntVar(win, value = 0, name ="x1"),IntVar(win, value = 0, name ="y1"),IntVar(win, value = 0, name ="x2"),IntVar(win, value = 0, name ="y2"), IntVar(win, value = 0, name ="c")
frame = ImageTk.PhotoImage(Image.open("hand.jpg"))  
line_counter = 0
def get_width(i,j):
    global angle
    j_left, j_right = j,j
    while True:
        if result_image[i][j][0]==Maxval:
            j_left = j
            j +=2
            break
        else:
            j -=1
    while True:
        if result_image[i][j][0]==Maxval:
            j_right = j
            j+=2
            break
        else:
            j +=1
    return j_left,j_right
            
def print_line(counter):
    x1_l, x1_r = get_width(y1.get(),x1.get())
    x2_l, x2_r = get_width(y2.get(),x2.get())
    angle,dx,dy,dyp,dxp,t1,t2 = 10,0,100,0,0,0,1
    if counter==1:
        if x2.get()-x1.get() != 0:
            m = (y2.get()-y1.get())/(x2.get()-x1.get())
            b = y1.get()-m*x1.get()
        else:
            m,b,dy,dyp,dxp,t1,t2 =1,0,50,50,0,1,0

        if line_counter == 5:
            dx,dxp =-10,10
        canvas.create_line(x1_l+10+dxp,y1.get(),x1_r+5+dx+dxp,y1.get(), fill="green", width=0.5)
        canvas.create_line(x2_l+10+dxp,y2.get(),x2_r+dx+5+dxp,y2.get(), fill="green", width=0.5)
        canvas.create_line(((t1*x1.get())+t2*(y1.get()+dy-b))/m,y1.get()+dy+dyp,(t1*x1.get())+(t2*(y1.get()-dy-b))/m,y2.get()-dy-dyp, fill="green", width=0.5)

def getPosition(event):
        x, y = event.x, event.y  
        global line_counter
        coordinates = "       -"
        global label
        label =Label(win, text=coordinates, font=('Calibri 5'))
        label.place(x=x,y=y)
        if counter.get() == 1:
            x1.set(0) # Get x-coordinate 
            y1.set(0) # Get y-coordinate
            x2.set(0) # Get x-coordinate 
            y2.set(0) # Get y-coordinate
            counter.set(0)       
        if (x1.get() ==0 and y1.get() ==0):
            x1.set(x) # Get x-coordinate 
            y1.set(y) # Get y-coordinate
        elif (x2.get() ==0 and y2.get() ==0):
            x2.set(x) # Get x-coordinate 
            y2.set(y) # Get y-coordinate
            counter.set(1)
            line_counter+=1
        print_line(counter.get())
        
# Create a canvas widget
global canvas
canvas=Canvas(win, width=397, height=406, cursor = "plus")
canvas.pack()

# Add a line in canvas widget
canvas.bind('<Button-3>', getPosition)
canvas.create_image(10,10,anchor=NW,image=frame)

win.mainloop()

def curve(image,row1,row2,dy1,dy2):
    #img = Image.open('image3.jpg').convert('L')
    img = Image.open(image)

    #img.save('image_3.jpg')
    ################### MAIN ALGORITHM ##########################
    image = cv2.imread(image)  # Load Image
    image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)  
    image_in_pixels = image.reshape((-1, 3))   # Reshape as 2D matrix:  W*H x 3  
    image_in_pixels = np.float32(image_in_pixels)   # convert to float

    #### Run KMeans using python OpenCV  
    _, pixels, (centers) = cv2.kmeans(image_in_pixels, 32, None, (cv2.TERM_CRITERIA_EPS + cv2.TERM_CRITERIA_MAX_ITER, 100, 0.2), 10, cv2.KMEANS_RANDOM_CENTERS)
    centers = np.uint8(centers)     # 8 bit integers
    pixels = pixels.flatten()     # flatten the labels array
    result_image = centers[pixels.flatten()] 
    result_image = result_image.reshape(image.shape) # reshape as normal image in 3D(W X H X RGB)

    xp1 = linspace(0,len(result_image[row1]),len(result_image[row1]))
    yp1 = []
    xp2 = linspace(0,len(result_image[row1]),len(result_image[row1]))
    yp2 = []
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,4), dpi=120) # 10 is width, 4 is height
    
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)  # (nRows, nColumns, axes number to plot)
    plt.imshow(img)
    
    # Left hand side plot
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)  # (nRows, nColumns, axes number to plot)
    for k in result_image[row1]:
        yp1.append(k[2]+dy1) 
    for l in result_image[row2]:
        yp2.append(l[2]+dy2) 

    print(dy2)
    plt.plot(xp1,yp1)  # green dots
    plt.title('Scatterplot Greendots')  
    plt.xlabel('X'); plt.ylabel('Y')
 #   plt.xlim(0, 6); plt.ylim(0, 12)

    # Right hand side plot
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    plt.plot(xp2,yp2)  # blue stars
    plt.title('Scatterplot Bluestars')  
    plt.xlabel('X'); plt.ylabel('Y')
#    plt.xlim(0, 6); plt.ylim(0, 12)
    
    plt.show()
